    <p class="text-gray-700">Look for skin-contact Grüner Veltliner from Austria's Weinviertel, Georgian Rkatsiteli from small producers, or orange-method Chenin Blanc from South Africa's Swartland region. These often deliver comparable textural complexity and aromatic interest at 40-60% less cost than famous Friulian producers. Portuguese Vinho Verde made with extended skin contact also offers excellent value for those seeking orange wine character without the premium pricing.</p>
